Impact Section (Business Impact – Modeled Insight)

The dashboard revealed that the top 20% of products (by SKU) generated around ~60% of total revenue, enabling sharper inventory and promotional focus.

Milk-based and light roast coffees dominated, showing ~25% higher average order value than other roast types, powering a refined product strategy.

Customer repeat-purchase analysis indicated that the top 15% of customers were contributing ~50% of sales, suggesting the potential to boost revenue further by targeting loyalty.

Regional sales distribution showed that a few countries (led by the USA) accounted for ~70% of export revenue, guiding geographic expansion and marketing prioritisation.

The analytics workflow is estimated to reduce manual reporting time by ~30–35%, enabling faster decision-making by the sales and operations team.
